HEADWORD: Latisternal
<hw>Lat`i*ster"nal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>latus</ets> broad + E. <ets>sternal</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having a broad breastbone, or sternum; -- said
of anthropoid apes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

